This paper focuses on reducing model size, computation, and power demands for enabling modern networks deployment on resource-constrained devices, such as always-on security cameras and drones. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a fast sensitivity test to effectively perform channel pruning, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
